previous.excerpt:
I forgot to name this doll during the episode. Whups! I guess she can keep the name ‘Sirena’. Thank you so much for joining me, and leave a comment with what animal theme we should tackle next! I’ll announce the poll over on the community tab, and through my socials. And I’ll try to update it here in the description box as well (if I remember!). 

Mentioned in video:
April Rose https://www.instagram.com/april.roseart/
@H ALI Crafts 
Festival Hair Extension tutorials: 
https://youtu.be/m7b474oFPlk
https://youtu.be/CNcQ1x4YRM8

Catch STOCK BOX Season 1: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLwf5az3O7M4c1lbRmvht4tRR88ZWKbYR-

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Materials:
Monster High Doll: Sirena Von Boo
Nylon doll hair from http://www.dollyhair.com/
Hair extension—I think the one I used was kanekalon hair. 
Reroot tool and needles from TheDollPlanet.com
Water Colored Pencils - Faber Castell
Pastels - Mungyo Hand-Rolled Soft Pastels
Acrylic paints – Liquitex, Alpha, Golden
Gouache cakes (paint) – Caran D’ache
Pearl Ex Powders
Air dry clay – La Doll
Sealant - Mr. Super Clear UV Flat by Mr. Hobby (wear a mask and spray in a ventilated area!)
Mask - Organic Vapor Particle Respirator Mask
Varnish (Duraclear)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Merchandise: https://www.zazzle.com/store/dollightful/collections
https://society6.com/dollightful
Doll clothing patterns here: https://www.etsy.com/shop/DollightfulPatterns
Instagram, Twitter, Pinterest: @dollightfully
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Musical tracks from Artlist https://artlist.io 
Runway by Veshza
Starry-eyed (instrumental version) by Jan & The Boy
In Viaggio Verso I’Alba by Andrea Musci
Jell-O (instrumental version) by Egozi
Slow Down by Steven Beddall
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Logo and other graphics designed by: https://charliesparksdesign.myportfolio.com/
